The paper discusses attacks on web applications and networks, which are typically studied in the computer security (cs.CR) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses practical defenses that can be deployed at the firewall level, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The attacks described in the paper require knowledge of the sequence numbers of both client and server in a TCP connection, which involves systems and control theory (cs.SY) concepts. Finally, the paper discusses the exploitation of a side channel, which is related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
